Break and Continue
# Break - exit loop
for i in range(10):
    if i == 5:
        break
    print(i)  # 0, 1, 2, 3, 4

# Continue - skip iteration
for i in range(5):
    if i == 2:
        continue
    print(i)  # 0, 1, 3, 4

Sets - Unique Collections
Sets is an unordered collection of unique elements; can be changed, but elements themselves must be immutable.
They‚Äôre ideal for membership testing, removing duplicates, and mathematical set operations.
# Creating sets
numbers = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
numbers = set([1, 2, 2, 3, 3])  # {1, 2, 3}

# Set operations
set1 = {1, 2, 3}
set2 = {3, 4, 5}

set1.union(set2)            # {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
set1.intersection(set2)     # {3}
set1.difference(set2)       # {1, 2}

# Adding/removing
numbers.add(6)
numbers.remove(1)






Important


Set are mutable and iterable.









Tip


Use {} or set() constructor to create set!

